column2: Spread angel wings blacker than your heart (or so you will doubtless say).
Spread your illusory─yet still impressive─golden wings.
Spread your wicked wings, realistic enough to fool any man─though voidsent are another matter.
Spread mischief and mayhem! Also, fae wings.
Don a pair of oval spectacles that do not improve your eyesight in any way.
Don a pair of tinted lenses and try not to bump into anything.
Don a pair of rectangular glasses for a classic illusion of intelligence.
Open a sabotender parasol. Inscrutable twirling recommended.
Spread mischief, mayhem, and your lovely aquamarine fae wings.
Don a pair of rose-colored spectacles and exude incurable optimism.
Open a tsukumogami parasol. Rest assured it's not an actual umbrella ghost...or is it?
Open a tactful taskmaster umbrella and <Emphasis>get back to work</Emphasis>.
Shoulder a knapsack and look the part of a seasoned traveler.
Spread trickery, deceit, and a graceful pair of fae wings.
Open a neon parasol─you'll be positively <Emphasis>glowing</Emphasis>.
Open a bomb parasol and make an explosive fashion statement.
Shoulder a Pelupack and assume the role of a roving peddler.
